# Expo injects EXPO_PUBLIC_* at bundle time. Rebuild the app after any change here.
# Base URL must end with /api (no trailing slash). Requests use paths like /mobile/login.
#
# Production URL for release APKs is set in `.env.production` (committed). Override locally
# with `mobile/.env` (gitignored) if you need a different server during dev.

# ─── Physical phone / production APK ─────────────────────────────────────
# Use your server's PUBLIC IP or DNS. Prefer nginx on staff (4603) or admin (4602)
# so /api is proxied to Node — do NOT use localhost on a real device.
#
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE=http://13.53.33.63:4603/api
#
# AWS / firewall: allow inbound TCP on that port (4603 or 4602) on the instance
# security group. Port 4601 (direct API) must also be open if you use :4601/api.
#
# Test from your PC (should return JSON):
#   curl -s http://13.53.33.63:4603/api/mobile/organizations
#
# Mobile login no longer blocks on duplicate Staff ID across orgs: the API picks one
# account deterministically unless you send optional `organizationId` in the login body.
#
# Then build a new APK so the env is baked in (needs Android SDK on the machine).
#
# Option A — Dev PC with Android Studio (simplest): open `mobile/android` in Android Studio
#   and Build > Generate Signed Bundle / APK, or from repo root:
#     npm run mobile:prebuild && cd mobile && npm run build:apk
#
# Option B — Headless Linux / EC2 (no adb needed): install Android SDK, then:
#     export ANDROID_HOME=/path/to/android/sdk   # e.g. $HOME/Android/Sdk after sdkmanager
#     export PATH="$PATH:$ANDROID_HOME/platform-tools"
#     cd mobile && npm ci && npm run prebuild:android && npm run build:apk:gradle
#   APK: mobile/android/app/build/outputs/apk/release/app-release.apk
#
# `npm run build:apk` runs `expo run:android` which requires adb — use `build:apk:gradle`
# on servers without a device/emulator.

# ─── Local dev (emulator/simulator on same machine as API) ───────────────
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE=http://localhost:4601/api

# ─── Android emulator → API on host ──────────────────────────────────────
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE=http://10.0.2.2:4601/api
